Installation Instructions
=========================

Copyright (C) searchingforstrangeness contributors.

This file describes how to set up and build the
searchingforstrangeness package inside a MicroBooNE ubana development area.
It is not a standalone autotools package.  Installation here means preparing
the source tree and building it in the expected MRB/LArSoft environment.  For
an overview of the repository, see README.  For running jobs after the build,
see USAGE.


Prerequisites
-------------

You need:

  * access to the MicroBooNE software container;
  * access to CVMFS and the standard MicroBooNE products;
  * an MRB development area;
  * a checkout of ubana;
  * the usual MicroBooNE command-line tools such as mrb and lar.


1. Enter the MicroBooNE container
---------------------------------

Run:

     apptainer shell \
            -B /cvmfs \
            -B /exp/uboone \
            -B /pnfs/uboone \
            -B /run/user \
            -B /etc/hosts \
            -B /etc/localtime \
            -s /bin/bash \
            --env UPS_OVERRIDE='-H Linux64bit+3.10-2.17' \
            /cvmfs/uboone.opensciencegrid.org/containers/uboone-devel-sl7

Then source the standard products:

     source /cvmfs/uboone.opensciencegrid.org/products/setup_uboone_mcc9.sh


2. Create an MRB development area
---------------------------------

For example:

     cd /exp/uboone/app/users/$USER/production/
     mkdir strangeness
     cd strangeness
     mrb newDev -q e17:prof
     source /exp/uboone/app/users/$USER/production/strangeness/localProducts_*/setup


3. Fetch ubana
--------------

Run:

     mrb g ubana
     cd srcs/ubana
     git checkout tags/v08_00_00_82


4. Adjust ubana compiler flags if needed
----------------------------------------

If the build environment requires warnings-as-errors to be disabled, edit:

     srcs/ubana/CMakeLists.txt

and remove or disable the WERROR setting while keeping the extra warning
suppression flags needed by the LibTorch-dependent code path.


5. Clone searchingforstrangeness
--------------------------------

Run:

     cd srcs/ubana/ubana
     git clone https://github.com/njlane314/searchingforstrangeness.git
     cd searchingforstrangeness
     source .setup.sh


6. Add this package to the ubana build
--------------------------------------

From the ubana source directory, append this package to the parent
`CMakeLists.txt`:

     cd ../../
     echo "add_subdirectory(searchingforstrangeness)" >> CMakeLists.txt


7. Build
--------

From the MRB top directory:

     cd $MRB_TOP
     mrbsetenv
     mrb i -j4


8. Optional helper-script workflow
----------------------------------

If your checkout includes the local helper scripts, the setup is often done by:

     cd srcs/ubana/ubana/searchingforstrangeness
     ./.container.sh
     source .setup.sh
     ./.build.sh


Installed files
---------------

The build system installs headers, sources, FHiCL files, and assets into the
MRB/LArSoft product area by way of the package `CMakeLists.txt` files.  The
package is intended to be used from that development environment, not through a
separate `make install` step in a generic system prefix.


After installation
------------------

Once the package is built, use USAGE for the checked-in runtime workflows and
scripts/README.md for dataset-handling notes.
